description: From Terpsichore (“the Muse of dance in Greek mythology”).

adjectives.description: terpsichorean (comparative more terpsichorean, superlative most terpsichorean)

examples: They're quiet enough in the morning hours,They're quiet enough in the afternoon,Reserving their terpsichorean powersTo dance by the light of the Jellicle Moon.

entries.meaning: A person who dances, especially professionally.
